00:13:36.560 --> 00:13:38.600
he asked me to include it in my talk.

00:13:40.960 --> 00:13:43.840
We need to grow support lines
and help groups,

00:13:44.480 --> 00:13:46.440
so victims can help each other

00:13:47.240 --> 00:13:50.056
when their lives and finances
have been derailed.

00:13:50.080 --> 00:13:54.456
We must as individuals disrupt
gender violence as it is happening.

00:13:54.480 --> 00:13:56.256
92 percent of young people

00:13:56.280 --> 00:13:58.080
29 and under witness it.

00:13:58.720 --> 00:14:01.200
72 percent of us have witnessed it.

00:14:02.080 --> 00:14:03.816
We must have the courage and urgency

00:14:03.840 --> 00:14:06.520
to practice stopping it
as it is unfolding.

00:14:08.240 --> 00:14:09.440
And lastly,

00:14:10.720 --> 00:14:11.920
believe her.

00:14:13.600 --> 00:14:14.816
Believe her.

00:14:14.840 --> 00:14:17.320
(Applause)

00:14:21.720 --> 00:14:25.560
This is fundamentally
a problem of human interaction.

00:14:26.560 --> 00:14:30.696
And as I believe that human interaction
is at the core of our healing,

00:14:30.720 --> 00:14:34.720
trauma not transformed
will be trauma transferred.

00:14:35.600 --> 00:14:38.696
Edith Wharton said,
"The end is latent in the beginning,"

00:14:38.720 --> 00:14:43.696
so we are going to end this talk
replacing hate speech with love speech.

00:14:43.720 --> 00:14:45.656
Because I get lonely in this,

00:14:45.680 --> 00:14:47.520
but I know that we are allies.

00:14:48.640 --> 00:14:50.296
I recently learned

00:14:50.320 --> 00:14:54.936
about how gratitude and affirmations
offset negative interactions.

00:14:54.960 --> 00:14:58.416
It takes five of those
to offset one negative interaction,

00:14:58.440 --> 00:14:59.896
and gratitude in particular --

00:14:59.920 --> 00:15:02.616
free, available globally
any time, anywhere,

00:15:02.640 --> 00:15:04.736
to anyone in any dialect --

00:15:04.760 --> 00:15:07.976
it fires the pregenual anterior cingulate,

00:15:08.000 --> 00:15:09.816
a watershed part of the brain

00:15:09.840 --> 00:15:12.456
that floods it with great, good stuff.

00:15:12.480 --> 00:15:15.096
So I'm going to say
awesome stuff about myself.

00:15:15.120 --> 00:15:17.456
I would like for you
to reflect it back to me.

00:15:17.480 --> 00:15:19.616
It might sound something like this --

00:15:19.640 --> 00:15:21.096
(Laughter)

00:15:21.120 --> 00:15:25.136
I am a powerful and strong woman,
and you would say, "Yes, you are."

00:15:25.160 --> 00:15:26.816
Audience: Yes, you are.

00:15:26.840 --> 00:15:28.576
Ashley Judd: My mama loves me.

00:15:28.600 --> 00:15:30.016
A: Yes, she does.

00:15:30.040 --> 00:15:32.096
AJ: I did a great job with my talk.

00:15:32.120 --> 00:15:33.736
A: Yes, you did.

00:15:33.760 --> 00:15:36.896
AJ: I have a right to be here.

00:15:36.920 --> 00:15:38.696
A: Yes, you do.

00:15:38.720 --> 00:15:39.936
AJ: I'm really cute.

00:15:39.960 --> 00:15:41.216
(Laughter)

00:15:41.240 --> 00:15:42.696
A: Yes, you are.

00:15:42.720 --> 00:15:44.456
AJ: God does good work.

00:15:44.480 --> 00:15:46.256
A: Yes, He does.

00:15:46.280 --> 00:15:48.016
AJ: And I love you.

00:15:48.040 --> 00:15:50.360
Thank you so much
for letting me be of service.

00:15:51.320 --> 00:15:52.536
Bless you.

00:15:52.560 --> 00:15:57.730
(Applause)

